com.randallscharpf.java.jmorsecoding.base.standards

Class DefaultMorseStandard

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.randallscharpf.java.jmorsecoding.base.standards.DefaultMorseStandard
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    MorseStandard

    public class DefaultMorseStandard
extends java.lang.Object
implements MorseStandard
    A MorseStandard implementation that returns the same timing and symbol set specifications whenever asked through its lifetime. Instances of this class are immutable.
    Since:
    1.0

    • Constructor Detail

      • DefaultMorseStandard

        public DefaultMorseStandard(MorseTiming timing,
                            MorseSymbolSet symbols)
        Creates a MorseStandard with the supplied timing and symbol set specifications. These specifications cannot be changed throughout the lifetime of the instance, and the results of getTimingSpecification() and getSymbolSpecification are exactly the parameters to this method.
        Parameters:
        timing - an object giving the timing parameters of the Morse Code protocol
        symbols - an object giving the symbol translation parameters of the Morse Code protocol
        Since:
        1.0

    • Method Detail

      • getTimingSpecification

        public MorseTiming getTimingSpecification()
        Gives the timing parameters of this Morse Code protocol. The object returned provides the lengths of dots, dashes, and gaps between them.

      • getSymbolSpecification

        public MorseSymbolSet getSymbolSpecification()
        Gives the symbol translation parameters of this Morse Code protocol. The object returned provides the set of dots and dashes for each written character in a word and each prosign.
        Specified by:
        getSymbolSpecification in interface MorseStandard
        Returns:
